author: Ehda M. Dagooc
title: VisayasMed raises the bar for healthcare in VisMin | The Freeman
text:
CEBU, Philippines — The VisayasMed Hospital has launched a state-of-the-art medical laboratory in partnership with Singapore Diagnostics (SGD), raising the bar for healthcare services not only for Cebuanos but for the entire Visayas and Mindanao regions.
Operated and managed by AppleOne Medical Group (AMG), the healthcare arm of the AppleOne Group of Companies, the facility is designed to cater to at least 1,000 patients a day.
"By teaming up with VisayasMed Hospital, we're able to empower and provide Cebuanos with expanded access to a diverse array of top-notch laboratory tests without needing to travel to Manila or overseas," said Ritche Joseph Manuel D. Evidente, President and chief executive officer (CEO) of Singapore Diagnostics.
The launching of the new medical laboratory reinforces AMG’s commitment to bring in world-class brands and building globally competitive facilities in Visayas and Mindanao and is part of AMG’s strengthened partnership with Singapore Diagnostics (SGD).
SGD will fully operate the laboratory, both inpatient and outpatient, through their well-trained medical technologists and laboratory specialists.
“AppleOne invests in hospitals and facilities, and partners with prestigious companies such as Singapore Diagnostics because we see how important investing in quality healthcare is. This is our way of helping elevate the quality of life of people in Cebu and the VisMin region,” said AppleOne CEO and President Ray Go Manigsaca.
With its collaboration with SGD, VisayasMed Laboratory further elevates healthcare for Cebuanos, now with the capacity to accommodate up to 1,000 patients a day. Offering over 450 cutting-edge tests, global quality laboratory standards, faster results, fully automated operations, and specialized training for scientists and medical technologists, this partnership marks a new era of excellence in healthcare, Manigsaca added.
VisayasMed Hospital, formerly Visayas Community Medical Center, boasts of nearly 70 years of healthcare excellence, delivering top-tier medical services having a comprehensive range of departments including family medicine, pediatrics, internal medicine, surgery, obstetrics, and gynecology, as well as specialized services in dermatology, psychiatry, ophthalmology, and anesthesiology.
On the other hand, SGD is the leading laboratory service provider in the Philippines and the flagship of Pathology Asia, setting global standards. It is the first Philippine laboratory accredited by the College of American Pathologists (CAP).
SGD is a powerhouse in healthcare as it has been awarded Diagnostics Provider of the Year by Healthcare Asia twice, and has been recognized for Service Innovation and Employee Engagement in 2024. With over 450 professionals across 47 locations nationwide, processing laboratory tests for over 600 hospitals, clinic labs, and healthcare institutions in the Philippines, and serving up to 100,000 patients every month, SGD is one of the top players in Philippine laboratories.
In line with AMG’s commitment to excellence, the VisayasMed Lab can serve up to 1,000 patients a day, ensuring timely and efficient healthcare delivery.
Singapore Diagnostics (SGD) has grown to be among the largest laboratories in the Philippines. Processing laboratory tests for over 300 hospitals, clinic labs, and healthcare institutions in the Philippines, SGD serves up to 50,000 patients every month.
Through this partnership, formally signed in April, 2023, VisayasMed Hospital will be able to carry out its main goal of providing a holistic patient experience by offering a more convenient and personalized approach to healthcare as SGD is known for its global expertise and technology.
In addition to its mission to provide world-class laboratory services, SGD also aims to become a well-equipped training venue for the best scientists of Cebu for the continuous improvement of medical services and quality healthcare.
AppleOne is a Cebu-based property developer known for its landmarks of strength and iconic partnerships, along with multi-awarded projects that compete on a global stage. Its vision and mission are deeply rooted in its desire to elevate the lives and living conditions of fellow Cebuanos.
AppleOne develops a portfolio of mixed-use/commercial establishments, office spaces, residential developments, hotels and resorts, and healthcare.

author: Nastya Bobkova
title: Microsoft Copilot para Mac: Inteligencia artificial en tu dispositivo
text:
Microsoft ha lanzado la aplicación Copilot para Mac, que permite a los usuarios trabajar con inteligencia artificial directamente a través del programa macOS.
Esto es lo que sabemos Copilot es la inteligencia artificial generativa de Microsoft basada en tecnologías OpenAI. Ofrece funciones similares a ChatGPT: los usuarios pueden obtener respuestas a preguntas, obtener ayuda con la programación, cargar imágenes para contextualizar, crear imágenes y texto, resumir información, realizar investigaciones, ejecutar comandos rápidos y mucho más.
En la versión para Mac, Copilot admite un tema oscuro, carga de imágenes, generación de contenidos y la función Think Deeper para un análisis más profundo. La aplicación no tiene compras dentro de la aplicación, pero ofrece acceso gratuito y una suscripción de pago a Copilot Pro. Esta última cuesta 20 dólares al mes y proporciona acceso a los últimos modelos de IA.
Se acabó la espera: ¡por fin podemos pasar el rato en macOS! Descarga Copilot para Mac y pruébame hoy mismo.
- Microsoft Copilot (@MSFTCopilot) 27 de febrero de 2025 Microsoft Copilot está disponible de forma gratuita en la Mac App Store. Funciona en todos los Mac con chips Apple Silicon que ejecuten macOS 14 o posterior.
Se sabe que Windows 11 permite integrar el iPhone en el menú Inicio para transferir archivos y mensajes. Esto es posible gracias a una nueva función que permite integrar el iPhone en el menú Inicio, lo que permite comprobar el nivel de batería, leer mensajes e incluso realizar llamadas o escribir mensajes.
Microsoft ha hecho gratuita la comunicación por voz con Copilot.

author: , Green Bay Press-Gazette
title: Check out photos of the Northern Lights last night from skywatchers across Wisconsin
text: Check out photos of the Northern Lights last night from skywatchers across Wisconsin Due to a rare, strong geomagnetic storm, Aurora Borealis may be visible again tonight. The Northern Lights graced night skies across Wisconsin and the U.S. on Thursday night after an eruption of solar material caused the [NOAA Space Weather Prediction](https://www.swpc.noaa.gov/news/g4-severe-storm-watch-10-11-october) to issue a [severe geomagnetic storm watch](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/local/2024/10/09/northern-lights-forecast-auroras-might-be-seen-in-wisconsin-thursday/75590287007/). Watches at this level are very rare. Strong geomagnetic storms can impact infrastructure, potentially disrupting communications, the electric power grid, navigation, radio and satellite operation, NOAA says. The watch continues into early Saturday morning, so if you missed the Aurora Borealis last night, you still may be able to see them tonight. But, if you can't catch the Northern Lights either night, you can enjoy these photos taken in Milwaukee and Wisconsin last night. More: [Northern lights could be visible in Wisconsin as part of a 'very rare' solar storm this week](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/local/2024/10/09/northern-lights-forecast-auroras-might-be-seen-in-wisconsin-thursday/75590287007/) What causes the Northern Lights? Also known as Aurora Borealis, the Northern Lights are [a natural light display in Earth's sky](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/nation/2024/05/10/northern-lights-aurora-when-time/73638964007/) that is famously best seen in high-latitude regions of the northern and southern hemispheres. The phenomenon is caused when electrically charged particles from space enter Earth's atmosphere and collide with [molecules and gasses like oxygen and nitrogen](https://www.jsonline.com/story/graphics/2024/05/18/northern-lights-colors-explained/73731506007/), causing the atmospheric particles to gain energy. To return to their normal state, the particles release that energy in the form of light, according to the [University of Alaska at Fairbanks, Geophysical Institute](https://www.gi.alaska.edu/monitors/aurora-forecast) website, which tracks the phenomenon. As Auroras form, Earth's magnetic field redirects the particles toward the poles through a process that produces a stunning display of rays, spirals and flickers that have fascinated humans for millennia. Whether hues of green, red, blue and pink dance about in the sky is due to the altitude in which the collisions occur, as well as the composition and density of the atmosphere at the time. When Northern Lights are active, the best time to see them is between 10 p.m. and 2 a.m. Are the Northern Lights becoming more common? This isn't the first time this year people throughout Wisconsin caught a glimpse of the Northern Lights. In May, a [powerful geomagnetic storm](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/nation/2024/05/10/severe-solar-storm-2024/73642315007/) unleashed [spectacular views of the northern lights](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/nation/2024/05/11/aurora-borealis-photos-northern-lights-seen-us-europe/73652013007/) in areas of the U.S. where Auroras are seldom visible, [including here in Milwaukee](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/local/2024/05/11/northern-lights-seen-in-milwaukee-wisconsin-last-night/73653382007/). As the [sun nears the height of its 11-year cycle](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/nation/2024/10/01/northern-lights-solar-maximum-auroras/75449249007/) in 2025, people across the world can expect more frequent and brighter Northern-Light activity due to increased electromagnetic activity. Best places in Wisconsin to see the Northern Lights Here's a list of places in Wisconsin that could offer some of the best views of the night sky: [Newport State Park](https://dnr.wisconsin.gov/topic/parks/newport), Ellison Bay [Driftless Region, Wisconsin](https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/2022/06/28/driftless-region-wisconsin-vernon-county-wants-become-international-dark-sky-park-kickapoo-valley/7487767001/) [Harrington Beach State Park](https://dnr.wisconsin.gov/topic/parks/harringtonbeach), Belgium [Kettle Moraine State Forest](https://dnr.wisconsin.gov/topic/parks/kms), Eagle [Kohler-Andrae State Park](https://dnr.wisconsin.gov/topic/parks/kohlerandrae), Sheboygan [Parnell Tower](https://dnr.wisconsin.gov/topic/parks/kmn/recreation/hiking), Plymouth Journal Sentinel reporter Alex Groth contributed to this report.

author: @WTOC11
title: Senator Ossoff raises concerns over Medicaid cuts
text:
Senator Ossoff raises concerns over Medicaid cuts
SAVANNAH, Ga. (WTOC) - Republicans in Congress are proposing $880 billion in cuts to the committee that oversees Medicaid. They say it’s part of a broader plan to reduce government spending and cut taxes.
But Senator Ossoff says these cuts could have devastating effects on children, seniors, and hospitals across the state.
Right now, Medicaid covers about 40% of all children, nearly half of all births, and about 70% of seniors in nursing homes.
Ossoff said slashing funds could put millions at risk of losing coverage and push more rural hospitals closer to shutting down.
As of last year, more than half of Georgia’s rural hospitals are struggling financially. Nine have closed, one stopped providing inpatient care, and 18 are at risk of shutting down.
Ossoff says Georgia’s long-standing refusal to expand Medicaid has already limited access to health care, and further cuts would only make the situation worse.
“I am sounding the alarm that these proposed drastic cuts to Medicaid will fundamentally damage the health and safety of my constituents in Georgia,” said Sen. Jon Ossoff, D-Georgia. “It will put kids at risk, pregnant women, and delivering mothers at risk, seniors in nursing homes at risk, and hospitals across our state into dire financial jeopardy.”
It’s unclear whether these cuts will actually happen. Just this week, President Trump said Medicaid “isn’t going to be touched.”
And some Senate Republicans are pushing back, saying the House proposal goes too far.

author: BeSoccer
title: El Brighton se acuerda de ganar y frena al Ipswich
text:
El Brighton, con goles de Kaoru Mitoma y Georginio Rutter, ganó al Ipswich Town (0-2) y frenó el resurgir de los locales, que sumaban 3 partidos consecutivos sin perder.
Los 'seagulls' se llevaron el partido en la segunda parte, cuando Mitoma mandó a la red un pase de Matt O'Reilly con un disparo en el que el portero del Ipswich, Christian Walton, pudo hacer mucho más.
A 8 minutos del final, Rutter convirtió a la media vuelta un balón muerto en el área. El VAR revisó la jugada por posible intromisión a la visión del portero en fuera de juego, pero el tanto subió al marcador y el Brighton sentenció su primera victoria en Premier League desde hace 9 jornadas. Venía de 4 empates seguidos y de no ganar en liga desde el 23 de noviembre.
Bien diferente era la dinámica para el Ipswich, que había ganado al Chelsea y empatado con el Fulham, además de derrotar al Bristol Rovers en la Copa. Los 'Tractores' marcan la salvación, con 16 puntos, los mismos que el Wolverhampton Wanderers, antepenúltimo, mientras que el Brighton tiene 31 unidades y mira a las posiciones europeas a cuatro de distancia.
